.TH CPPTEST 1 "February 2026" "2.2" "CppTest Manual"
.SH NAME
cpptest \- Advanced competitive programming testing utility
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cpptest
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR] [\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Automated testing tool for C++. Supports isolation, custom checkers, clang-tidy, and multiple compilers.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i ", " \-\-in-place
Run tests directly in the source directory. Default behavior is to clone the folder to \fI/tmp/cpptest/tmp\fR for isolation.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-fast
Skip static analysis (clang-tidy) and formatting checks (clang-format) for faster execution.
.TP
.BR \-F ", " \-\-fix
\fBAuto-Fix Mode.\fR Automatically applies \fIclang-format -i\fR and \fIclang-tidy --fix\fR to the source code before testing. \fBNote:\fR This modifies your files! It also forces \-\-in-place mode.
.TP
.BR \-R ", " \-\-no-comments
\fBRemove Comments.\fR Creates a temporary copy of the source code, removes all single-line and multi-line comments, and runs tests on the clean version. Does not modify the original file.
.TP
.BR \-K ", " \-\-force-checker
Force usage of \fIcheck.cpp\fR. Returns error if \fIcheck.cpp\fR is missing.
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-force-diff
Force usage of standard \fI.out\fR file comparison (diff), ignoring \fIcheck.cpp\fR even if it exists.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-select
Select default compiler from installed list.
